description: -Which soap?It is a gentle, re-greasing and moisturizing goat's milk oats honey soap with slight exfoliation efffekt through the oatmeal.-Phoenix soaps - production, ingredients and without fragrances:Our soaps are made in small batches exclusively manually by our freelancers in our factory and do not contain any preservatives or other chemicals; they are biodegradable.Our goat's milk, selected by local farmers, contains numerous vitamins such as:B12, B6, B1 and A as well as C&E minerals and caprylic acid, which are responsible for soothing the skin and are supposed to bring about a real makeover.Oatmeal as well as alpha-hydroxy acids (AHA) reduces wrinkles, signs of aging, peels the skin and are often used in expensive luxury cosmetics.Of course, our freelancer could have made the soap more beautiful, but he would have had to mix a lot of preservatives, perfumes and colors into it.This is exactly what he wanted to avoid and chose the natural soap, which also contains no fragrances.-well-maintained hands even in these times:At the moment we have to wash and cream our hands all the time.Due to the numerous washing processes in these times, our hands become leathery, cracked and stretching very often. Expensive creams need to be made to soothe the skin.Simply wash your hands with the honey oatgo goat's milk soap after each wash and you no longer need cream, the skin is sealed, soothed and nourished with a gently absorbing natural fat.- the soap may seem expensive to some, but it is still genuine handmade and without chemical additives.Only the natural ingredients that are indicated are used here, which means that you know exactly what is contained in the soap.- why the soap is not colorful:The brown color of the soap is automatically derived from the reaction of the goat's milk with the lye.All other goat's milk soaps that are not brown have colour additives, some and also with artificially produced mica powder, which has been chemically produced and consists of most of plastic.Here, artificial colours were deliberately dispensed with.- the soap becomes firmer the more often you use it and releases even more vitamins for the skin.- People with main problems have always given me positive feedback and are now regular customers.Stop lubricating chemical soaps on your skin, the ingredients of which you have not googled and whose effect on the skin you do not know.If you have any questions, you can contact us now and at any time.I am very happy to answer your questions.Packing:Delivery always 3 soap pieces / bars, approx.: 177 gr - we like to add something ;)

name: Necklace Triskele Triple Spiral Wood Burned
description: Unique men's or ladies wooden necklace.Triple spiral(Druidism): Derived from the Greek word "Triskeles" meaning "three legs", the Triskele or Triple Spiral is a complex ancient Celtic symbol. Often referred to by many as a Triskelion, its earliest creation dates back to the Neolithic era, as it can be seen at the entrance of Newgrange, Ireland. The Triskele gained popularity in its use within the Celtic culture from 500BC onwards. This archaic symbol is one of the most convoluted to decipher as symbolists believe it is reflective of many areas of culture from the time.1)The motion of action, cycles, progress, revolution and competition.2)Life-death-rebirth, spirit-mind-body, mother-father-child, past-present-future, power-intellect-love and creation-preservation-destructionIt’s thought that through the combination of these two areas we gain one meaning of the Celtic triskele. It is believed to represent a tale of forward motion to reach understanding. However, this is thought not to be the only meaning, as it is also believed to represent three Celtic worlds; the spiritual world, the present world and the celestial world. Like the ancient Trinity knot, the number 3 holds a special symbolism within the triskele.Material:Wood: Beech WoodCord:  Cotton Waxed CordVarnish: Odorless Wood Varnish for children's toysApproximate Dimensions:Size:  35mm x 35mm x ~5mmCord Size: AdjustablePlease note that this item is handmade, so there may be small differences comparing with the photo.If you have any inquiries, please don’t hesitate to contact me. name: Rare Unusual 1930s Circular 900 Silver Gold Wash Vintage Blood Red Bohemian Garnet Ring Signed Size 6 3/4 UK N EU 54
description: Fantastic and unusual, this Bohemian garnet circular ring in 900 (stamped) silver is signed T B with the German Iron cross ( which dates back to the 19th Century) in between the letters.  This ring is unusual in that the garnets are enclosed in a silver circle.  There are two tiers of pave set garnets with the top one taking the form of a flower.  It has had a gold wash and some of this has worn off the back of the shank.  Otherwise it is in very good condition.  It will fit a US 6 3/4 size UK N EU 54.Red garnets have been mined in the Bohemian  Hills of Czechoslovakia since the 16th century.  These pyrope garnets reached their height of  popularity in jewelry of the Victorian era. Although the  deposits had been generally regarded as depleted, today a  small mining operation is working on garnetiferous gravels near the  village of  Podsedice, northwest of  Prague.

name: Antique Jade Chinese Export Cloisonne Enamel Butterfly Moth Carved Floral Jadeite Filigree Silver Ring Size: US 9 UK R 1/2 EU 60 1960s
description: A wonderful chunky vintage Chinese filigree silver ring set with a large oval dark green Jadeite cabochon that has been carved into a floral pattern.  The shoulders are accented with colourful Cloisonne enamel depicting a butterfly or moth on each side and taper to a plain shank.  The ring is stamped with silver on the inside of the shank, will fit a size: US 9 UK R 1/2 EU 60 and is in good vintage condition; there are two holes in the cabouchon but these jadeite pieces seem to have originated as hat ornaments over a hundred years ago and the holes were there to enable them to be sewn on.  The ring itself was made in the 1960s from one of these pieces.Jade is often considered synonymous with China and the country´s appreciation of both Nephrite and Jadeite can be traced back by about 8,000 years.  Jadeite was first imported into China from across the border with Myanmar, not later than the Ming Dynasty, ca. 1475.  Originally jadeite was traded mainly out of the Royal palace and when the Empress Dowager Cixi ruled China at the end of the Qing Dynasty (1861 to 1908) she started to collect high quality jadeite from all over the country.  This trend also swept over the whole royal family and the nobility and, by 1908, jadeite was the most expensive jade sold in Beijing’s most famous antique market, Liu Li Chang. Jadeite and Nephrite have shared a high market status ever since.

name: Four Tier 900 European Silver Vermeil Gold Wash Vintage Czech Blood Red Bohemian Garnet Ring Size 6 3/4 UK N EU 54 3D Unisex 1960s
description: This is a wonderful vintage ring from the 1960s made of 900 silver which has had a gold Vermeil wash and is encrusted with blood red Bohemian Garnets.  There are four tiers of prong set pave design Bohemian garnets rising in ovals that decrease in size in Edwardian style, up to the last single garnet in the centre.  The inside of the shank is stamped 900 with the rabbit's head 3 for Czech made in the 1960s and G for Granat Turnov, the Bohemian Garnet manufacturer.  It will fit a size: US 6 3/4 UK N EU 54 and is in very good vintage condition.Red garnets have been mined in the Bohemian  Hills of Czechoslovakia since the 16th century.  These pyrope garnets reached their height of  popularity in jewelry of the Victorian era. Although the  deposits had been generally regarded as depleted, today a  small mining operation is working on garnetiferous gravels near the  village of  Podsedice, northwest of  Prague.
